description:
Company Insight:

Spun out from one of the oldest names in HFT Equities, one of the fastest-growing prop trading firms is looking to grow its multi-asset trading and research platform across North America and APAC. Their robust infrastructure has allowed them to identify fundamental value in global financial markets, combining scientific rigour with creative research to build cutting-edge trading strategies.

They are currently looking for a quantitative engineer to drive the backbone of their entire research process. You’ll play a critical role in running simulations, monitoring strategy performance, and continuously improving the team's research infrastructure.

Fluent or professional-level proficiency in Mandarin is required.

Principal Responsibilities:
• Implement and maintain strategy models, while improving strategy backtesting frameworks;
• Develop quantitative research toolchains;
• Maintain quantitative databases and develop strategy monitoring & risk analysis tools;
• Deploy strategy code and optimize execution logic.

Technical Skillset:
• Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Financial Engineering, or related technical fields;
• 1-3 years of professional programming experience in production environments;
• Proficient in C++ or Python programming languages;
• Familiarity with modern data engineering ecosystems is a plus;
• Prior experience handling financial data preferred;
• Quantitative research/trading experience preferred;
• Ability to think critically, rapidly, and rigorously;
• Effective communicator with a strong teamwork mindset;
• Self-motivated and thrives in fast-paced environments.

Pre-Application
• Please do not apply if you're looking for a contract or remote work.
• Please ensure you meet the required experience section prior to applying.
• Allow 1-5 working days for a response to any job enquiry.
• Your application is subject to our privacy policy, found here: https://www.thurnpartners.com/privacy-policy
